 4 British holidaymakers were stranded overnight on an impounded cruise ship in Lisbon harbour after its owners were served with a summons for an allegedly unpaid debt .
The ship had been set to leave Lisbon at 7 pm on Tuesday night with its 489 passengers heading back to Bristol Avonmouth .
But lawyers slapped a court order on the ship over an ` unresolved ' and ` historic ' financial wrangle .